{"title": "Revolving Door Revolution", "content": "Sometimes a nation undergoes a major revolution, and completely changes its style of government. Sometimes people lose faith in the new style of government, and have another revolution soon after. Sometimes this happens over and over and over again, and that's the Revolving Door Revolution.\n\nThe reasons for this can be complex. Maybe the nation in question is extremely polarized in popular opinion? Maybe the successive governments aren't stable, or effective enough to last? Maybe the writers just think it makes for better drama (or better laughs, depending)?\n\nThese sorts of turnovers are particularly common in your stereotypical Banana Republic.\n\nSee also Full-Circle Revolution, where the new government is run by different people but policy-wise winds up being no different than the old. In a Revolving Door Revolution situation, successive governments may well be polar opposites.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RevolvingDoorRevolution", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BenoitBrisefer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Tintin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/RobinSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/LadyShiva", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarWarsExpandedUniverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/NewJediOrder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LegacyOfTheForce", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/FateOfTheJedi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Legacy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/QuantumOfSolace", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheAvengers2012", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ItCantHappenHere", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/WilliamButlerYeats", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DavidDrake", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/RCN", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Eldraeverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HarryHarrison", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BlakesSeven", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBible", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/ForgottenRealms", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Junta", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.p